line_2: On shelf of deal beside the cuckoo-clock,

line_1: THE Queen of Birds, t'encrease the Regal Stock,
line_2: Had hatch'd her young Ones in a stately Oak,

line_1: Let happier friends divide my farmer's stock,
line_2: Cut down my grain, and shear my little flock;

line_1: Twitcher, a rotten branch of mighty stock,
line_2: Whose interest winds his conscience as his clock:

line_1: These are the grafters of your royal stock
Book, beads, and maple-dish his meagre stock,
line_2: His dwelling a recess in some rude rock,

line_1: He calls forth children from the barren stock;
line_2: He calls forth living waters from the rock;

line_1: Ah! no; a shepherd of a different stock,
line_2: And far unlike him, feeds this little flock:

line_1: And measur'd out her little stock.
line_2: The remnant of her cloth she took,

line_1: A decent offering from his little stock,
line_2: Fruits of the ground, or firstlings of his flock:
Grows drowsy as the clicking of a clock.
